<title type="html"><![CDATA[4/21(Sat. ) Watching movies with subtitles &amp; cultural immersion (Host:Ken)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=159&amp;p=173#p173"><![CDATA[
4/21(Sat. ) Watching movies with subtitles &amp; cultural immersion (Host:Ken)<br /><br />Topic 1: Watching movies with subtitles<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F_PQvy9xKNw&amp;t=21s">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F_PQvy9xKNw&amp;t=21s</a><!-- m --><br /><br /> 1.Do you watch English movies with subtitles? Do they help?<br /> 2. What's your favorite movie genre for English learning? Why?<br /> 3.Why are most Taiwanese much better at reading than listening? What's wrong with the way we learn?<br />4.How to get to understand English movies without subtitles?<br /><br />Topic 2: cultural immersion <br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4DzdVbkN-1E">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4DzdVbkN-1E</a><!-- m --><br /><br /> 1. Why is cultural immersion important for English learning?<br /> 2. Will learning a language abroad for a year make you more fluent?<br /> 3. Is there any way to get foreign language immersion without going aboard?<br /> 4. How to get rid of Chinese thinking? How to stop translating in your head?<br /><br />Saturday's meeting place:<br />Position: Dante coffee Shop (丹堤咖啡), MRT板南線 - 新埔站2號出口, next to 7-Seven, <br />板橋民生路二段237 號, <br />Time: PM 7:00-9:30, <br />minimum charge of Dante coffee for Royal English club attendant NT$80 (丹提低消80元)<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500.請帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=872">Shuman</a> — Tue Apr 17, 2018 6:37 am</p><hr />
